incorrect or that the loop processing `Indices` does not properly account for the
alignment constraints.\n\n### 2. Analyzing `opt`'s Log\nThe `opt` log shows that
the SLP vectorizer is attempting to vectorize a horizontal reduction. The
`computeExtractCost` function is invoked to estimate the cost of extracting
subvectors. The issue arises when processing the `Indices` array, which contains
values `{0, 14}`. The second value, `14`, combined with `EltsPerVector` (6),
results in an out-of-bound access relative to the aligned vector size
